[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1327},["Reactive",2],{"content-query-3S16vBwK6h":3},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"body":10,"_type":1322,"_id":1323,"_source":1324,"_file":1325,"_extension":1326},"/docs/core-tech/atomic-swap","core-tech",false,"","Atomic Swap","Atomic swap is performed between Beam and other cryptocurrency. Denote it BTC, but actually it can denote other network that supports the needed functionality.",{"type":11,"children":12,"toc":1313},"root",[13,20,25,32,37,63,68,156,187,193,206,216,227,232,237,250,257,266,293,299,323,410,416,453,559,568,603,609,615,985,991,1298,1304],{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":16,"children":17},"element","p",{},[18],{"type":19,"value":9},"text",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":21,"children":22},{},[23],{"type":19,"value":24},"The swap is performed in a single transaction, which effectively transfers the ownership of the Beam UTXO in exchange for some secret, which is needed to claim the being-exchanged coin on the BTC network.",{"type":14,"tag":26,"props":27,"children":29},"h1",{"id":28},"high-level-design",[30],{"type":19,"value":31},"High-level design",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":33,"children":34},{},[35],{"type":19,"value":36},"There are two parties:",{"type":14,"tag":38,"props":39,"children":40},"ul",{},[41,53],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":43,"children":44},"li",{},[45,51],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":47,"children":48},"strong",{},[49],{"type":19,"value":50},"A",{"type":19,"value":52},"lice. Owns the Beam, interested to trade it for the BTC",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":54,"children":55},{},[56,61],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":57,"children":58},{},[59],{"type":19,"value":60},"B",{"type":19,"value":62},"ob. Owns the BTC, interested to trade it for the Beam.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":64,"children":65},{},[66],{"type":19,"value":67},"There are 3 major phases of the atomic swap",{"type":14,"tag":69,"props":70,"children":71},"ol",{},[72,90,138],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":73,"children":74},{},[75,77],{"type":19,"value":76},"Prerequesites\n",{"type":14,"tag":38,"props":78,"children":79},{},[80,85],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":81,"children":82},{},[83],{"type":19,"value":84},"The being-exchanged UTXOs are locked on both networks for a specific time period (in terms of blocks).",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":86,"children":87},{},[88],{"type":19,"value":89},"Parties monitor both networks to ensure the source UTXOs are indeed locked.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":91,"children":92},{},[93,95],{"type":19,"value":94},"Exchange\n",{"type":14,"tag":38,"props":96,"children":97},{},[98,109,118,129],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":99,"children":100},{},[101,103,107],{"type":19,"value":102},"Parties collaborate to create a transaction that transfers the locked Beam to ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":104,"children":105},{},[106],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":108}," in exchange for the secret.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":110,"children":111},{},[112,116],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":113,"children":114},{},[115],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":117}," substitutes the secret to the transaction and finally broadcasts it to the network.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":119,"children":120},{},[121,123,127],{"type":19,"value":122},"Once transaction is visible - ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":124,"children":125},{},[126],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":128}," learns the secret.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":130,"children":131},{},[132,136],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":133,"children":134},{},[135],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":137}," creates a BTC transaction to claim the BTC UTXO, and broadcasts it to the BTC network.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":139,"children":140},{},[141,143],{"type":19,"value":142},"Rollback. In case the swap didn't take place (for whatever reason)\n",{"type":14,"tag":38,"props":144,"children":145},{},[146,151],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":147,"children":148},{},[149],{"type":19,"value":150},"Locked UTXOs on both network should remain intact until their lock timeout expires.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":152,"children":153},{},[154],{"type":19,"value":155},"After the timeout expiration parties broadcast transactions that transfers the locked UTXOs back to them.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":157,"children":158},{},[159,161,165,167,173,175,179,181,185],{"type":19,"value":160},"Note that ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":162,"children":163},{},[164],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":166}," actually claims the BTC UTXO ",{"type":14,"tag":168,"props":169,"children":170},"u",{},[171],{"type":19,"value":172},"after",{"type":19,"value":174}," sending the Beam UTXO. This means that the lock timeout of the BTC UTXO must be significantly bigger than that of the Beam UTXO, because ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":176,"children":177},{},[178],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":180}," may broadcast the Beam transaction just before the timeout expires, the ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":182,"children":183},{},[184],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":186}," should still have enough time to build and broadcast the BTC transaction.",{"type":14,"tag":26,"props":188,"children":190},{"id":189},"technical-design",[191],{"type":19,"value":192},"Technical design",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":194,"children":195},{},[196,198,204],{"type":19,"value":197},"The ",{"type":14,"tag":199,"props":200,"children":201},"em",{},[202],{"type":19,"value":203},"unlock secret",{"type":19,"value":205}," is the SHA-256 hash preimage (i.e. a 256-bit value which, after hashing, should be equal to a known 256-bit value). Supported on Beam, BTC, and, probably, many other networks.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":207,"children":208},{},[209,214],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":210,"children":211},{},[212],{"type":19,"value":213},"Note",{"type":19,"value":215},": The drawback of this scheme is a considerable privacy compromise. As we'll see, it's possible for the attacker to detect such an atomic swap, by looking for the matching hash preimages in both networks.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":217,"children":218},{},[219,221,225],{"type":19,"value":220},"There is a better option, where the ",{"type":14,"tag":199,"props":222,"children":223},{},[224],{"type":19,"value":203},{"type":19,"value":226}," is an EC scalar, i.e. private key. It's based on the so-called aggregate signatures. It's less generic, since it assumes both networks use the same EC equation and the Generator.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":228,"children":229},{},[230],{"type":19,"value":231},"So we'll review the scheme with the Hash-lock, but keep in mind that it can easily be modified to the one with the aggregate signature, and the rest of the argument, and the general flow are exactly the same.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":233,"children":234},{},[235],{"type":19,"value":236},"There are no scripts in Beam blockchain. However the following is supported in the transaction kernel:",{"type":14,"tag":38,"props":238,"children":239},{},[240,245],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":241,"children":242},{},[243],{"type":19,"value":244},"Timelock - minimum blockchain height for the kernel to be valid",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":246,"children":247},{},[248],{"type":19,"value":249},"HashPreimage",{"type":14,"tag":251,"props":252,"children":254},"h2",{"id":253},"utxo-lock-on-btc-network",[255],{"type":19,"value":256},"UTXO lock on BTC network",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":258,"children":259},{},[260,264],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":261,"children":262},{},[263],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":265}," broadcasts a BTC transaction, which creates an UTXO which can be spent under the following conditions:",{"type":14,"tag":69,"props":267,"children":268},{},[269,278],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":270,"children":271},{},[272,274],{"type":19,"value":273},"Timeout + secret key chosen by ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":275,"children":276},{},[277],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":279,"children":280},{},[281,283,287,289],{"type":19,"value":282},"Hash preimage chosen by ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":284,"children":285},{},[286],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":288}," + secret key chosen by ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":290,"children":291},{},[292],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":14,"tag":251,"props":294,"children":296},{"id":295},"utxo-lock-on-beam-network",[297],{"type":19,"value":298},"UTXO lock on Beam network",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":300,"children":301},{},[302,304,308,310,314,316,321],{"type":19,"value":303},"This part is somewhat more complex, since there are no scripts in Beam. ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":305,"children":306},{},[307],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":309}," and ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":311,"children":312},{},[313],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":315}," collaborate to create a ",{"type":14,"tag":199,"props":317,"children":318},{},[319],{"type":19,"value":320},"shared",{"type":19,"value":322}," UTXO, whose blinding factor is shared between them.",{"type":14,"tag":69,"props":324,"children":325},{},[326,340,377,405],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":327,"children":328},{},[329,333,334,338],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":330,"children":331},{},[332],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":309},{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":335,"children":336},{},[337],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":339}," randomly choose their parts of the blinding factor for the shared UTXO",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":341,"children":342},{},[343,347,348,352,354,358,360],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":344,"children":345},{},[346],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":309},{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":349,"children":350},{},[351],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":353}," first create the \"rollback\" transaction, which would transfer the shared UTXO back to ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":355,"children":356},{},[357],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":359}," if the exchange didn't take place.\n",{"type":14,"tag":38,"props":361,"children":362},{},[363,368],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":364,"children":365},{},[366],{"type":19,"value":367},"This transaction kernel is Time-locked, i.e. transaction can only be broadcasted starting from specific blockchain height.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":369,"children":370},{},[371,375],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":372,"children":373},{},[374],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":376}," saves this transaction, but doesn't broadcast yet.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":378,"children":379},{},[380,384,385,389,391,395,397],{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":381,"children":382},{},[383],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":309},{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":386,"children":387},{},[388],{"type":19,"value":60},{"type":19,"value":390}," create the transaction that spends ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":392,"children":393},{},[394],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":396},"'s UTXO and creates the shared one.\n",{"type":14,"tag":38,"props":398,"children":399},{},[400],{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":401,"children":402},{},[403],{"type":19,"value":404},"The tricky part is creating the Bulletproof for the shared UTXO. Takes 3 iterations.",{"type":14,"tag":42,"props":406,"children":407},{},[408],{"type":19,"value":409},"They broadcast this transaction to the Beam network, to create the shared UTXO.",{"type":14,"tag":251,"props":411,"children":413},{"id":412},"exchange-transaction",[414],{"type":19,"value":415},"Exchange transaction",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":417,"children":418},{},[419,421,425,427,432,434,438,440,445,447,451],{"type":19,"value":420},"At this point both Beam and BTC UTXOs are locked, both parties get confirmations for this. In addition ",{"type":14,"tag":46,"props":422,"children":423},{},[424],{"type":19,"value":50},{"type":19,"value":426}," knows the ",{"type":14,"tag":199,"props":428,"children":429},{},[430],{"type":19,"value":431},"Image",{"type":19,"value":433}," of the locked BTC UTXO. Now they collaborate to build a Beam transaction that transfers the shared (locked) Beam UTXO to ",{"type":1